ren":[{"type":"text","value":"AS"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"ct-403174"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" runner\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"line","line":10},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"line","line":11},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"ct-230219"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"COPY"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"ct-403174"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" --from=builder /usr/share/zoneinfo/Asia/Seoul /etc/localtime\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"line","line":12},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"ct-230219"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"RUN"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"ct-403174"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" echo "}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"ct-639592"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\"Asia/Seoul\""}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"ct-403174"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" > /etc/timezone"}]}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"style","children":[{"type":"text","value":".ct-460403{color:#6F42C1;}\n.dark .ct-460403{color:#FFCB6B;}\n.ct-403174{color:#24292E;}\n.dark .ct-403174{color:#A6ACCD;}\n.ct-639592{color:#032F62;}\n.dark .ct-639592{color:#C3E88D;}\n.ct-166744{color:#6A737D;}\n.dark .ct-166744{color:#464B5D;font-style:italic;}\n.ct-172800{color:#005CC5;}\n.dark .ct-172800{color:#82AAFF;}\n.ct-944198{color:#032F62;}\n.dark .ct-944198{color:#89DDFF;}\n.ct-466387{color:#D73A49;}\n.dark .ct-466387{color:#89DDFF;}\n.ct-230219{color:#D73A49;}\n.dark .ct-230219{color:#F78C6C;}"}]}],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[{"id":"set-up-timezone-in-alpine-linux","depth":2,"text":"Set up timezone in Alpine linux","children":[{"id":"install-tzdata-package","depth":3,"text":"Install tzdata package"},{"id":"copy-the-proper-zone-info-to-localtime","depth":3,"text":"Copy the proper zone info to localtime"},{"id":"specify-timezone","depth":3,"text":"Specify timezone"},{"id":"check-the-datetime-with-date-command","depth":3,"text":"Check the datetime with date command"}]},{"id":"optimize-docker-image","depth":2,"text":"Optimize docker image","children":[{"id":"optional-with-multi-stage-builds","depth":3,"text":"(Optional) With multi-stage builds"}]}]}},"_type":"markdown","_id":"content:en:blog:2023:06:6.setting-the-timezone-in-alpine.md","_source":"content","_file":"en/blog/2023/06/6.setting-the-timezone-in-alpine.md","_extension":"md"},{"_path":"/blog/2023/06/can-i-use-pm2-with-docker","_dir":"06","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"en","_empty":false,"title":"Can i use PM2 inside Docker?","description":"I recently re-checked the project I created when I didn't know Docker at all and found that I was using PM2 inside Docker. It didn't fit the best p...","createdAt":"2023-06-01 12:50","updatedAt":"2023-06-02 12:51","cover":"https://wbwsloxpaolxwerwiupa.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-asset/images/ae8bac97-8438-4261-a322-f03bd84de1fe.webp","tags":["Docker","PM2","Wiki"],"body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I recently re-checked the project I created when I didn't know Docker at all and found that I was using PM2 inside Docker.\nIt didn't fit the best practices mentioned in the Docker document, but I thought it might be an exception, so I investigated it."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"monitoring-becomes-difficult"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Monitoring becomes difficult."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Since PM2 takes charge of the task that Docker was doing, it becomes difficult to monitor CPU/Memory metrics in Docker.\nIn addition, even if the service dies, it will not be known from Docker because it will restart in PM2.\nTherefore, normal monitoring cannot be performed in the monitoring system (Cloudwatch, etc.)."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"it-goes-against-dockers-best-practice"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It goes against Docker's best practice."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As a best practice mentioned in the official document, it is recommended to use "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"one service per container"}]},{"type":"text","value":" for separation of concern.\nTherefore, using PM2 internally for clustering is not a very good example."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"See "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"/blog/2023/05/one-service-per-container-docker"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Why is it recommended to run only one process in a container?"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"docker-and-pm2-are-interchangeable"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Docker and PM2 are interchangeable."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The main purposes of using PM2 include clustering, abnormally terminated process restart, and logging.\nThis can be replaced to some extent in Docker, where clustering can be replaced by docker-compose's "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"scale"}]},{"type":"text","value":" command, abnormally terminated process restart can be replaced by "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"restart policy"}]},{"type":"text","value":", and logging can be replaced by "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"logs"}]},{"type":"text","value":" command.\nTherefore, it would be better to choose and use it according to the situation rather than using more computing resources by using both."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"conclusion"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Conclusion"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you check the PM2 document "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://pm2.keymetrics.io/docs/usage/docker-pm2-nodejs/","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Docker Integration"}]},{"type":"text","value":", it will be possible to implement it.\nHowever, based on the above, I found that using PM2 inside Docker does more harm than good.\nTherefore, I will conclude that "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"it is better not to use PM2 inside Docker"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and conclude the article."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"reference"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Reference"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/51191378/what-is-the-point-of-using-pm2-and-docker-together","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"what is the point of using pm2 and docker together?"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://www.docker.com/blog/keep-nodejs-rockin-in-docker/","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Top 4 Tactics To Keep Node.js Rockin’ in Docker"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://docs.docker.com/config/containers/multi-service_container/","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Run multiple services in a container"}]}]}]}],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[{"id":"monitoring-becomes-difficult","depth":2,"text":"Monitoring becomes difficult."},{"id":"it-goes-against-dockers-best-practice","depth":2,"text":"It goes against Docker's best practice."},{"id":"docker-and-pm2-are-interchangeable","depth":2,"text":"Docker and PM2 are interchangeable."},{"id":"conclusion","depth":2,"text":"Conclusion"},{"id":"reference","depth":2,"text":"Reference"}]}},"_type":"markdown","_id":"content:en:blog:2023:06:4.can-i-use-pm2-with-docker.md","_source":"content","_file":"en/blog/2023/06/4.can-i-use-pm2-with-docker.md","_extension":"md"},{"_path":"/blog/2023/05/one-service-per-container-docker","_dir":"05","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"en","_empty":false,"title":"Why is it recommended to run only one process in a container?","description":"In the Docker document recommends the use of one service per container for separation of areas of interest as a best practice. In addition, many do...","createdAt":"2023-05-31 12:29","updatedAt":"2023-05-31 12:29","cover":"https://wbwsloxpaolxwerwiupa.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-asset/images/4cd3d3ce-3b28-4867-b6d1-49c05b17f7a9.webp","tags":["Docker","Wiki"],"body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"blockquote","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It’s best practice to separate areas of concern by using one service per container."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Docker documentation"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://docs.docker.com/config/containers/multi-service_container/","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In the Docker document"}]},{"type":"text","value":" recommends the use of "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"one service per container"}]},{"type":"text","value":" for separation of areas of interest as a best practice.\nIn addition, many documents online mention this a lot, so why encourage the use of one service per container?"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"benefits-of-running-a-single-service-per-container"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Benefits of running a single service per container"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Scalability"}]},{"type":"text","value":": It makes it much easier to scale specific services as needed."},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nIf multi-services are operated in one container, even the same service may require different settings for each container when horizontally expanding.\nIn this case, it may be more complicated than when the docker is not used."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Reusability"}]},{"type":"text","value":": The service becomes much easier to reuse in other projects that require it."},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nIf multi-services were run in one container, they would not be available in other projects because they are specialized in the project."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Portability and Predictability"}]},{"type":"text","value":": Since the scope of work reduced, it becomes much easier to debug security patches or errors."},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nIf multi-services are operated in one container, other non-patch-related services in the container may also be affected when applying security patches due to the high degree of combination between services.\nTherefore, it may be necessary to perform tasks that would not have been necessary for a single service per container configuration. This means that portability is low, and predictability is also low because it is relatively difficult to predict the range of effects of errors."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"disadvantages-of-running-multi-service-per-container"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Disadvantages of running multi-service per container"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Log processing"}]},{"type":"text","value":": If multi-services are run in one container, it is difficult to identify which service is output from.\nTherefore, additional settings should be made to enable identification, or logs should be redirected to a separate file."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Monitoring"}]},{"type":"text","value":": Docker performs container health checks with PID 1.\nTherefore, if PID 1 is normal when driving multi-services, it may not be detected even if the rest of the process is terminated due to an error."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"conclusion"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Conclusion"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It was confirmed that it was better to configure a container with a single service due to the advantages of single service per container + the disadvantages of multi-service  per container.\nOne thing that I regret is that I wanted to check what would happen if there was an exception, but I couldn't record it because there were no significant examples. If I find a good example later, I will add it."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"reference"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Reference"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://www.tutorialworks.com/containers-single-or-multiple-processes/","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Containers: one single process, or multiple processes?"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://twitter.com/testdrivenio/status/1447958997785399300","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Docker best practice:"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://devops.stackexchange.com/questions/447/why-it-is-recommended-to-run-only-one-process-in-a-container","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Why it is recommended to run only one process in a container?"}]}]}]}],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[{"id":"benefits-of-running-a-single-service-per-container","depth":2,"text":"Benefits of running a single service per container"},{"id":"disadvantages-of-running-multi-service-per-container","depth":2,"text":"Disadvantages of running multi-service per container"},{"id":"conclusion","depth":2,"text":"Conclusion"},{"id":"reference","depth":2,"text":"Reference"}]}},"_type":"markdown","_id":"content:en:blog:2023:05:3.one-service-per-container-docker.md","_source":"content","_file":"en/blog/2023/05/3.one-service-per-container-docker.md","_extension":"md"}]